1.) Install Node.js

2.) Go to terminal and run:
  node -v
  
3.) In terminal create your project folder:
    mkdir <project name>
    
4.) cd to your <project name> and in your terminal:
    mkdir backend
    cd backend
5.) Create a package.json file in the folder by running:
    npm init -y
    
6.) Install a few dependencies by running:
    npm install express cors mongodb dotenv
    
7.) Install nodemon:
    npm install -g nodemon
    
NPM PACKAGES

cors- Provides and express middleware that can enable CORS with different options so we can make the right connections on the network

mongodb- Allows us to interact with the MongoDB database

dotenv- Loads environmental variables from the process.env file instead of setting them on our development machine

nodemon- Automatically detects code changes and restarts the Node server
